{
  "doc_id": "23751",
  "text": "ALT and AST are two liver enzymes that reflect hepatocyte integrity. Liver enzymes leak into the bloodstream by liver injury and increase their levels in serum, which reflects hepatocyte injury [CITATION_1] . The elevated ALT and AST levels were recovered following IH treatment in both fibrotic models, which suggested that IH protected hepatocytes from chronic injury. In parallel, IH treatment alleviated inflammation infiltration in liver sections. Our previous study also showed that IH inhibited hepatocyte apoptosis and autophagy induced by inflammation, thereby improving liver function [CITATION_2] . It indicated that the hepatoprotective role of IH could be attributed to the anti-inflammation effect [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
